#v(0.3cm)

*Title:* Research on Literary Reception Activities Through Theatrical and Musical Forms at Nguyen Huu Canh High School, Binh Tri Dong Ward.

*Student:* Ngo Thi Thu Nga

*Major:* Theory and Methodology of Literature Teaching — Code: 8.14.01.11

*Supervisor:* Dr. Tran Thanh Binh

#v(0.5cm)

*Purpose:* This thesis investigates the current state of literary reception activities through theatrical and musical forms and proposes pedagogical strategies to enhance students' literary appreciation competencies and academic performance in Vietnamese Literature at Nguyen Huu Canh High School, Binh Tri Dong Ward, Ho Chi Minh City.

*Research Methods:* The thesis employs a combination of theoretical research, empirical surveys, pedagogical experimentation, and statistical analysis methods.

*Findings:*

The thesis systematizes the theoretical foundations of literary reception, theatricalization, and music integration in high school Literature teaching. Based on empirical survey data collected at Nguyen Huu Canh High School, the study identifies the current status, influencing factors, and challenges in organizing literary reception activities through theatrical and musical forms. Subsequently, the thesis proposes an organizational process and specific pedagogical strategies, validated through pedagogical experiments to confirm their feasibility and effectiveness.

*Keywords:* literary reception, theatricalization, music in education, Literature teaching, high school, experiential learning.

